OL,3,CFamilies welcome the Chancellor's
OL,4,Cdecision to scrap the two-child
OL,5,Cbenefit cap
OL,7,FFamilies across the South West have
OL,8,Fwelcomed the decision to scrap the two-
OL,9,Fchild benefit cap.
OL,11,FIn her budget, Chancellor Rachel
OL,12,FReeves said "families are finding
OL,13,Ftimes hard" and "children shouldn't
OL,14,Fhave to bare the brunt of that".
OL,16,FShe confirmed that the two-child
OL,17,Fbenefit cap would be scrapped in full
OL,18,Ffrom April.
